1 b. Health or safety would be seriously threatened if a condition existing at the time
2 the petition was filed continues.
3 Appointment of receiver.
4 If the court grants the petition to place the mobile home park into receivership, the court
5 shall appoint the commissioner as receiver. The commissioner may designate a qualified
6 individual or a nonprofit organization to execute the receivership. An individual designated to
7 execute the receivership may not be employed by this state or a political subdivision. The
8 receiver shall use the income and assets of the mobile home park to maintain and operate the
9 mobile home park and to attempt to correct the violations of chapter 23 - 10, the administrative
10 rules of the department, or other condition which constitutes a threat to health or safety. The
11 receiver may not liquidate the assets of the mobile home park.
12 Termination of receivership.
13 The receivership terminates when:
14 1. The receiver and the court certify the conditions that prompted the receivership are
15 corrected;
16 2. The license to operate the mobile home park is restored;
17 3. A new license to operate a mobile home park is issued; or
18 4. The owner of the mobile home park discontinues operation and the residents of the
19 mobile home park have secured other appropriate housing.
20 Accounting.
21 Upon termination of the receivership, the receiver shall render a complete accounting to the
22 court and shall dispose of surplus funds as the court directs.
